# =============================================================================
# application-local-config.yml — PERSISTENT PER-SERVICE OVERRIDES (edit by hand)
# =============================================================================
#
# WHAT THIS FILE IS FOR
#   Service-local configuration that must SURVIVE every `ansiblew` run. The other
#   config files in this directory (e.g. application.yml, *-config.properties) are
#   REGENERATED on each run from inventory and MUST NOT be hand-edited — your
#   changes there are lost. This file is the opposite: Ansible creates it ONCE and
#   NEVER overwrites it (`force: no`), so anything you set here persists.
#
# HOW THE OVERRIDE WORKS
#   This service's container starts Spring Boot with:
#       -Dspring.config.additional-location=/data/<service>/config/
#       -Dspring.config.name=application,application-local-config,...
#   Spring loads `application-local-config` AFTER the generated config, so any
#   property you set here OVERRIDES the generated value. Use standard Spring YAML.
#
# NOTES
#   - Keep this file out of version control if it holds secrets.
#   - For environment-level overrides (passwords, JVM heap) use .env-custom in the
#     docker-compose dir instead. See docs/configuration.md.
#
# EXAMPLES (uncomment and adjust to the service):
#   # logging:
#   #   level:
#   #     au.org.ala: DEBUG
# =============================================================================
